- "stepped up to the plate at least once" refers to having at least one batting statistic record (COUNT(b.stat_id) > 0); 
- A defensive shift in baseball is a strategic defensive alignment; 
- wOBA (weighted On-Base Average) is a sabermetric statistic that measures a player's overall batting ability.

- A "seasoned player" refers to a player with extensive experience; in this context, it's quantified by having at least 500 at-bats, implying they are veteran players; 
- "Home run rate" is a measure of a player's power, calculated as home runs per 100 at-bats; 
- "Defensive shifts" are tactical moves where fielders position themselves non-traditionally to defend against a batter's tendencies; 
- "wOBA (Weighted On-Base Average)" measures a player's total offensive value and is a key metric in evaluating player performance.
